<a id="assignment" class="anchor" href="#assignment" aria-hidden="true"><span aria-hidden="true" class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>Assignment</h3>

<p>The purpose of this project was to build a lightweight Twitter clone written in Ruby that was well engineered and scalable. Our goal was to create a service that could support thousands of users following one another and posting, liking, and replying to tweets. The resulting application is hosted on <a href="http://secret-shelf-78111.herokuapp.com/front">Heroku</a> and uses a Postgres database and a Redis cache provided by Heroku. </p>

<p>To run your own copy of our nanoTwitter service, all you need to do is clone the repository, push it to a Heroku application with a database and Redis set up, and perform the initial database rake. Enjoy!</p>

